HEADWORD: Dcime
<hw>D⟦eacute⟧`cime"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>A French coin, the tenth part of a franc, equal to about two cents
(around 1900). In 2001 all previous French coins were superseded by the
euro.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

